# ♛ Chaturanga — Four Player Chess

A browser-based, real-time **4-player team chess** game built on Firebase Realtime Database.

## 🎯 Rules
- **4 players**, **2 teams**: Red + Blue (Team A) vs Green + Gold (Team B)
- Turn order: Red → Blue → Green → Gold → repeat
- Standard chess rules apply per player
- A player is eliminated when checkmated; their pieces remain on the board for their ally to consider
- **Team wins** when both opponents are eliminated or the last king is captured

## 🚀 Setup

### 1. Firebase Project
1. Go to [Firebase Console](https://console.firebase.google.com)
2. Create a new project
3. Go to **Realtime Database** → Create database (start in test mode)
4. Go to **Project Settings** → Add Web App → copy config

### 2. Configure
Open `index.html` and replace the Firebase config block:

```javascript
const firebaseConfig = {
  apiKey: "YOUR_API_KEY",
  authDomain: "YOUR_PROJECT.firebaseapp.com",
  databaseURL: "https://YOUR_PROJECT-default-rtdb.firebaseio.com",
  projectId: "YOUR_PROJECT_ID",
  storageBucket: "YOUR_PROJECT.appspot.com",
  messagingSenderId: "YOUR_SENDER_ID",
  appId: "YOUR_APP_ID"
};
```

### 3. Database Rules
In Firebase Console → Realtime Database → Rules, paste the contents of `firebase-rules.json`.

### 4. Deploy to GitHub Pages
```bash
git init
git add .
git commit -m "Initial commit"
git branch -M main
git remote add origin https://github.com/YOUR_USERNAME/chaturanga4.git
git push -u origin main
```
Then enable GitHub Pages under Settings → Pages → Branch: main.

### 5. Embed in Google Sites
Use the **Embed** widget with your GitHub Pages URL:
`https://YOUR_USERNAME.github.io/chaturanga4/`

## 📁 File Structure
```
index.html          ← Main entry point
css/style.css       ← Dark navy + wooden board styles
js/engine.js        ← Firebase sync, UI orchestration
js/gamelogic.js     ← Chess rules, move generation
js/renderer.js      ← Canvas board renderer
js/pieces.js        ← SVG-style piece drawing
firebase-rules.json ← Firebase security rules
README.md
```

## 🎮 How to Play
1. Open the URL and enter your name
2. Select your color (Red/Blue = Team A, Green/Gold = Team B)
3. Share the **Room ID** with your 3 friends
4. Friends enter the same Room ID to join
5. Game starts automatically when you interact — no waiting lobby needed
6. Use **Team Chat** to strategize with your partner
7. Use **Public Chat** to taunt your enemies 😄

## 🔧 Hosting Note
This game uses ES Modules (`type="module"`).  
You **cannot** open `index.html` directly from the filesystem — use a local server:
```bash
npx serve .
# or
python3 -m http.server 8080
```
